Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at Guilford Technical Community College in North Carolina about the American Jobs Plan. She highlighted the progress made by the administration, such as the vaccination campaign and economic relief efforts. The American Jobs Plan aims to create millions of jobs, particularly in infrastructure, and ensure that every worker has access to good jobs. Harris emphasized the importance of education and training after high school, and the need to invest in workforce development. She also stressed the significance of strong unions and improving communities through investments in broadband and water infrastructure. Harris concluded by expressing the administration's determination to pass the American Jobs Plan and build a better future for America.